<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-549] Add &apos;persistent filesets&apos; disclaimer to LOM</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-549</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18357&quot; title=&quot;Support multiple filesets per nodemap&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18357&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18357&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; offers a new approach to set filesets across the cluster permanently. Previously, &lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param -P&lt;/tt&gt; had to be used. Starting with Lustre 2.17, this is no longer required such that &lt;tt&gt;lctl nodemap_set_fileset&lt;/tt&gt; can be used as the primary command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param -P&lt;/tt&gt; can have unexpected side effects, this should be documented in the Lustre Operations Manual.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
